	<h1 class="spacer-t spacer-b-md font-bold tracking-[-0.0125em] text-white text-heading-xl">
		Understanding the Importance of Website Maintenance
	</h1>

	<div class="details space-y-8 spacer-b-md">

		<p>A well-maintained website is one of the most valuable assets your business has online. Modern websites rely on complex, interconnected technologies that need regular attention to stay secure, fast, and reliable. Without ongoing care, small issues can quietly compound into costly problems.</p>

		<h2 class="font-bold tracking-[-0.0125em] text-white text-heading spacer-t-xs">Why Annual Maintenance Fees?</h2>

		<p>Your maintenance plan covers a range of essential services, all handled on your behalf:</p>

		<ol class="space-y-4">
			<li><strong class="font-semibold text-white/90 block">Regular Updates:</strong> Every two weeks, I install updates to your Content Management System (CMS) to keep it running efficiently. Critical updates are applied immediately to guard against emerging threats.</li>

			<li><strong class="font-semibold text-white/90 block">Security and Performance:</strong> I manage your web hosting, apply security patches, and renew SSL certificates to keep your website secure. I also monitor uptime minute by minute and proactively investigate any issues that arise.</li>

			<li><strong class="font-semibold text-white/90 block">Monitoring and Fixes:</strong> Broken links harm your credibility and SEO. I monitor and fix these as part of regular SEO health checks, and address any bugs that appear to keep everything running smoothly.</li>

			<li><strong class="font-semibold text-white/90 block">Backups:</strong> I back up your website files and database daily, storing copies in multiple secure locations to protect against data loss.</li>

			<li><strong class="font-semibold text-white/90 block">Support:</strong> Whenever you need a small change, have a question, or need advice about your website or online presence, I'm here. I typically respond within one business day.</li>
		</ol>

		<p>Neglecting regular maintenance has real consequences. I've seen websites fall so far behind on updates that critical security fixes could no longer be applied, leaving them exposed to serious threats. In some cases, the only solution was a full rebuild from scratch.</p>

		<p>By investing in regular maintenance, you avoid those outcomes and the far greater costs that come with them. Your online presence is in good hands, and I'm always just an email away.</p>

